  • How is the security cameras wifi connection strength?

    After multiple WiFi and signal tests, its signal is very strong. If you had to draw a straight line from the router to the camera, the distance between them would be about 20-30 feet.

  • How do I connect this camera, please? What about its night vision?

    Connected via Wi-Fi,the connection is faster and more stable when using the latest trigger chip,Once connected, always connected.Enhance night vision by wearing glasses for improved nighttime viewing.

  • How often do you have to charge the batteries?

    If you turn the sensitivity all the way off,it will many months without charging. Tested!! We tested that the camera can be triggered 3500 times when fully charged. If it is activated multiple times in a day, it can last for a month.

  • How are the wireless security camera recharged?

    The outdoor camera wireless come with a usb plug in cord. You can charge through a wall oulet, or charge through usb port on your computer.

  • How many mega pixels are the security cameras wireless ? Can it monitor the license plate?

    Yes,The indoor/oudoor camera has a 2-megapixel color sensor, 135 diagonal field of view, up to 2K ( 2304 x 1296 ) at 30 frames/sec, High Dynamic Range (HDR), and H.264 encoding.

      One of the Best Wireless Security WIFI Camera!!!

      Style: 2 Camera System
      1.
      I recently received a set of two Wi-Fi cameras from Amazon Prime, and they arrived in just two days. Right out of the box, they exude a high-quality feel and impressive craftsmanship. After charging them for about three hours, I inserted 64GB micro-SD cards (not included,... See more
      I recently received a set of two Wi-Fi cameras from Amazon Prime, and they arrived in just two days. Right out of the box, they exude a high-quality feel and impressive craftsmanship. After charging them for about three hours, I inserted 64GB micro-SD cards (not included, but not necessary) and installed the steel mounting plates to monitor both the front of my house and my backyard. Here are my observations:

      The Vico-Home app is user-friendly and recognized the cameras immediately, making setup a breeze.
      Each camera features a strong magnetic base, allowing for easy mounting on any metal surface or with the included steel plates. They are completely wire-free.
      The price is very reasonable, offering great value considering their quality and functionality.
      These cameras capture the clearest images Ive experienced with any security system over the years.
      The motion detection is highly responsive, effectively capturing all movement even at medium sensitivity.
      With a large battery capacity, the cameras can last for months without needing a recharge. I opted to use a solar panel (not included) for the front camera, which is mounted 10 feet high. For the backyard, I simply attached the stand-alone camera to a tree using the included steel base, and its battery has held up remarkably well.
      Cloud storage is free for three days. If you want longer retention (up to one month) and extended recording times (up to 30 seconds instead of the basic 10 seconds), you can opt for a monthly subscription. However, accessing recordings via the internal micro-SD card (up to 128GB) is also an option.
      Overall, these cameras provide excellent value for the money and outperform any security systems Ive used in the past.

    • Lisa
      4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Good quality video, accurate motion detection
      Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2024
      Style: 2 Camera System
      These are super easy to install if you use battery power; if you've got something steel to stick to, it should take just a few minutes to set up and adjust the angle. If you don't have something steel, they include small steel plates you can screw into the wall. The... See more
      These are super easy to install if you use battery power; if you've got something steel to stick to, it should take just a few minutes to set up and adjust the angle. If you don't have something steel, they include small steel plates you can screw into the wall. The magnets are very powerful, the camera is not going to move unless you move it. The rubber plug which covers the SD card slot / USB-C / power button fits tightly and should keep weather out, and that plug itself has a plug in it the size of the included USB-C power cord to keep the weather out even if it's always connected to external power. The video quality is very good. The audio is intelligible. The app is very easy to use. It allows 2-way conversation, and if you hit the "alarm" button on the app an alarm goes off on the camera which is surprisingly loud.

      The system doesn't work unless you subscribe to VICOHOME's cloud service, but a 2-year basic subscription is included with the camera purchase. You can upgrade to a more expensive plan to get longer cloud storage (free plan deletes clips after 3 days) and AI motion detection, which is supposed to reduce false alarms, but the way my house is situated I don't get any false alarms with the free system. My biggest complaint is that the system is set up to only record short clips after detecting motion (10s - 20s for the "basic" subscription). This is understandable for cloud recording, but with the current firmware the camera only records to the SD card what it sends to the cloud. With support for 128GB SD cards, the camera should have the option to record all motion to the card. I suggested this their support, and they quickly wrote back agreeing that was a good idea and would pass it up to their development team. If have no idea if they'll follow through, but at least customer service is responsive.

      BOTTOM LINE: Good camera for the price. It will be even better if they change the firmware to allow unlimited-length recording via the SD card slot.
